<p><strong>有一天我会要个孩子的，但不是以我整个人生为代价，那样的话我会狠那个孩子一辈子的，我可能永远都不会爱他。</strong></p>
<p><strong>一种只会攻击女人的病，把她们变成家庭主妇的病。</strong></p>
<h2 id="never-rarely-sometimes-always">Never, Rarely, Sometimes, Always</h2>
<p>background: A pair of teenage girls in rural Pennsylvania travel to New York City to seek out medical help after an unintended pregnancy. -- from Letterboxd</p>
<p>some questiones you might ask:</p>
<p>Is abortion allowed in the United States?<br>
Due to the victory of Roe v. Wade, the United States allows women to have abortions if certain conditions are met, and the specific laws vary from state to state. But the U.S. Supreme Court overturns Roe v. Wade decision legalizing abortion in 2022.<br>
And the film's premiere is January 24, 2020 at Sundance Film Festival.</p>
<p>Why Autumn needs to go from Pennsylvania to New York?<br>
New York, where a minor doesn't need parental permission to obtain an abortion, unlike in her home state.</p>
<p>影片中有三个场景让我触动：<br>
第一个是Autumn在做检查时，镜头从医院的病房内慢慢切换到无垠的蓝天；<br>
第二个是Autumn与顾问Kelly的对话，也是影片片名Never, Rarely, Sometimes, Always的出处；<br>
第三个是Autumn的表姐Skylar为了筹钱，不惜将自己的身体出卖给旅途中搭讪的一个男人。</p>
